Both it and the neighboring spring of Aganippe were sup· posed to inspire those who drank ot' their waters. Juvenal calls Pegasus ‘Gorgoneas caballus' (iii. 118); but in most classical writers the term is contemptuous; its derivatives in modern languages lep„ ‘chevet' ‘cavalier‚' ‘cavalry 'l have entirely lost that shade of mean· ing.
